<% content_for(:title) { "Privacy Policy - Happy Pages" } %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="bg-white shadow sm:rounded-lg px-6 py-8 sm:px-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>

      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-6">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">1. Who we are</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Happy Pages Ltd ("we", "us", "our") operates the Happy Pages referral platform
            at <strong>app.happypages.co</strong>. We provide referral program tools for
            e-commerce merchants via Shopify.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">2. Data we collect</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            When a merchant installs our Shopify app, we access limited customer data
            through Shopify's APIs to operate the referral program:
          </p>
          <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 mt-4">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm font-medium text-gray-500">Data</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm font-medium text-gray-500">Purpose</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Customer email</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Unique identifier for referral tracking; links referrals across sessions</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Customer first name</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Personalisation of referral pages and codes (e.g. "JOHN847")</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Shopify customer ID</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Links referrals to the correct Shopify customer record</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Order data (order ID, discount codes used)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-700">Determines when a referral code has been used and triggers rewards</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            We do <strong>not</strong> collect phone numbers, shipping addresses, payment
            information, or full order history.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">3. How we use data</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We use collected data solely to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>Generate and track referral codes for customers</li>
            <li>Detect when a referral code is used on an order</li>
            <li>Issue discount rewards to referring customers</li>
            <li>Display personalised referral pages</li>
            <li>Send referral lifecycle events to merchant-configured integrations (e.g. Klaviyo)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">4. Data storage and encryption</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Data is stored in a PostgreSQL database hosted on Railway (US-based infrastructure).
            Personally identifiable information (email, first name) is encrypted at rest using
            Rails Active Record Encryption. API credentials and access tokens are also encrypted.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">5. Data retention</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We retain customer data for as long as:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>The merchant's app installation remains active, <strong>or</strong></li>
            <li>A customer requests deletion (processed within 30 days)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-3">
            When a merchant uninstalls the app, all associated data (referrals, analytics events,
            rewards, and credentials) is permanently deleted within 48 hours via Shopify's
            <code class="text-sm bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">shop/redact</code> webhook.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">6. Data sharing</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            We do not sell or share customer data with third parties. Data may be sent to
            merchant-configured integrations (such as Klaviyo or Awtomic) only at the
            merchant's explicit request and using the merchant's own API credentials.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">7. Customer rights</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Customers of merchants using our app can exercise their data rights through
            Shopify's built-in privacy tools. When a customer requests data access or
            deletion through Shopify, we receive and process the request automatically:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li><strong>Data access requests</strong> are logged and fulfilled within 30 days</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion requests</strong> result in anonymisation or removal of all PII</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">8. Merchant responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Merchants using our app are responsible for including our data processing in
            their own privacy policies and for ensuring they have a lawful basis to share
            customer data with our platform.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">9. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
            communicated to merchants via the app dashboard.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3">10. Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            For privacy inquiries, data requests, or concerns:
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
            <strong>Email:</strong> support@happypages.co<br>
            <strong>Company:</strong> Happy Pages Ltd
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
